    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 8'>
      <style />
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98222' id='7' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98882' x='559' y='889'>
            <zone h='98222' id='5' type-v2='layout-basic' w='87709' x='559' y='889'>
              <zone h='65778' id='3' name='Suitability_Heatmap' w='87709' x='559' y='889'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='32444' id='9' type-v2='text' w='71368' x='559' y='66667'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='14'>TREE × SOIL SUITABILITY MATRIX</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>The geographic map shows WHERE each species can grow across Ireland. This matrix shows WHY — scoring every species-soil combination on </run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>a scale of 1 (unsuitable) to 5 (optimal).</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>KEY INSIGHTS</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Sitka Spruce is uniquely suited to Peat (5) — the only species scoring above 2 on Ireland&apos;s dominant western soil. This explains why Sitka Spruce dominates 50%+ of Irish commercial plantings.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Beech and Douglas Fir share Fine Loamy as their optimal soil (5) — both are good choices for Ireland&apos;s lowland midlands.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>No species scores 5 on every soil — diversification across the  Afforestation Scheme is essential. A monoculture strategy locks the programme into specific regions.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Western Hemlock performs well across most textures (4–5) but scores just 2 on Peat — limiting its western Ireland deployment.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='32444' id='10' type-v2='text' w='16341' x='71927' y='66667'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>HOW TO READ THIS CHART</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>- Rows = the 5 modelled species</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>- Columns = soil texture types (Irish Soil Information System)</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>- Dark green = optimal match (5)</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>- Yellow = moderate (3)</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>- Red = poor match (1–2)</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' italic='true'>- Larger numbers = stronger species-soil compatibility</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10' italic='true'>DECISION IMPLICATIONS</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10' italic='true'>For each hectare of land, a planner can consult this matrix to select the highest-scoring species given local soil texture — moving from intuition to data-driven assignment.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
            <zone fixed-size='160' h='98222' id='6' is-fixed='true' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='11173' x='88268' y='889'>
              <zone h='7222' id='8' name='Suitability_Heatmap' pane-specification-id='0' param='[federated.09yf0q4193zx3y1abprav1emqbf6].[avg:Calculation_0923717839933483:qk]' type-v2='color' w='11173' x='88268' y='889'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
